<DIV class=3Dhide id=3DprojDescript1>This is considered the most =
important factor=20
when we consider a project for hosting on SourceForge.net. Submitted =
description=20
should be at least two paragraphs in length, and provide details of your =

intended implementation. This description, along with the Trove =
Categorization,=20
will be the basis for the approval or rejection of your request for =
project=20
hosting on SourceForge.net, and later, to ensure that you are using the =
services=20
in the intended way.</DIV>
<DIV class=3Dhide id=3DprojNameTip>This is the descriptive name for your =
project. It=20
will be the name that site users associate with your project.</DIV>
<DIV class=3Dhide id=3DprojUnixNameTip>UNIX name will be used for your =
project's=20
unique URL.</DIV>
<DIV class=3Dhide id=3DprojTakeover1>If you choose to become the new =
project=20
administrator, you must continue its maintenance and development within =
the=20
project's initial goals. When filling out the "Registration Description" =
field,=20
specify your background with the project, why you wish to take over its=20
development, and your future goals for the project.</DIV>
<DIV class=3Dhide id=3DprojTakeover2>You can replace a project that has =
been=20
registered under the same name if the project is suitable for removal =
(must have=20
no file releases, no CVS/Subversion activity, and be sufficiently =
old).</DIV>
