<DIV class=3Dsf_register_project_stage1_tricky_do><TEXTAREA =
name=3Dregistration_description rows=3D8 cols=3D80>For the initial =
conception, see =
http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/clueless/2008/02/odf-ooxml-nfoworks-for-har=
mony.asp

There are activities to develop translations among open-standard formats =
such as ODF, OOXML, and UOF (the Chinese standard for office documents), =
and some of those projects are here on SourceForge (odf-converter and =
uof-translator).  The new b2xtranslator project may also provide useful =
input to other translator projects, although its focus is on de factor =
binary formats, not open-standard ones.

The unique focus of nfoWorks is on (1) starting with tiny subsets that =
work; (2) only adding "safe" features as they are identified and their =
inter-translation is confirmed; (3) providing a way to identify that a =
document relies on a selection of safe features in a way, yet to be =
worked out, that protects users from inadvertently introducing =
incompatibilities; and, (4) relying on neutral technology and portable =
code wherever possible and only using freely-available tools.   =
</TEXTAREA><BR>
<DIV style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; WIDTH: 600px; COLOR: #666666">Please =
